<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="455" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d455">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760C.6215/545: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Willys</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-15T18:00:00+01:00">October 15, 1931—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 15—5:45 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>105. Minister of Foreign Affairs expresses concern over campaign in the
                            United States in respect of Corridor question which in turn is having
                            disquieting effect upon public opinion in Poland. He asks me to appeal
                            to you to use your influence with the American press to abate this
                            disturbing publicity.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Willys</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>